&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Harbinger&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Harbinger is an American commercial electric vehicle (EV) company on a mission to transform an industry starving for innovation. Harbinger’s best-in-class team of EV, battery, and drivetrain experts have pooled their deep experience to bring a first-of-its-kind EV platform to support the growing demand for medium-duty EVs and Hybrids. Harbinger: Familiar Form, Revolutionary Foundation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking someone with high attention to detail to join our team. As a Data Specialist, you will have various opportunities to contribute to &lt;strong&gt;improving our systems &amp;amp; data at the company&lt;/strong&gt;. The primary responsibilities for this position will be &lt;strong&gt;ensuring our systems are accurate, up to date, and are ready for scale&lt;/strong&gt;. The role also offers the opportunity to build valuable experience at a fast paced, high growth startup during a critical early product development stage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Input:&lt;/strong&gt; Transferring data from paper-based documents or other digital formats into our ERP system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Verification:&lt;/strong&gt; Reviewing and validating data for accuracy, completeness, and consistency with source documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Maintenance:&lt;/strong&gt; Updating existing records, correcting errors, and ensuring data integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirement Gathering:&lt;/strong&gt; Work with stakeholders to understand business needs and document system requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt; Analyze existing data and reporting, identify issues, and propose improvements or new solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Testing and Implementation:&lt;/strong&gt; Test and implement new or updated systems, ensuring they meet requirements and function correctly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree program or greater in Business Administration, or/and Relevant Degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to Detail: Data entry with high attention to detail to minimize errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organizational Skills: Keeping data organized and easily accessible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Computer Systems: Proficiency in using databases, spreadsheets, and other data management tools. Preferred ERP system (NetSuite) and Google Sheets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication Skills: Effectively communicating with team members to resolve data discrepancies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Problem-Solving Skills: Identifying and resolving data inconsistencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Rate:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;$33 - $36/hr&lt;/p&gt;
