&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10–15 years of experience in progressive HR roles, with a heavy emphasis on HRBP, People Ops, L&amp;amp;D, and program launches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in translating high-level business goals into actionable, scalable HR programs from scratch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of hypergrowth environments and the unique scaling challenges faced by fast-paced startups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent emotional intelligence, humility, and communication skills; you must be highly receptive to feedback and lead with deep empathy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong desire and acumen for getting deep into Harbinger’s business and building programs from those principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with commercial EV, automotive, or hardware manufacturing organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with the distinct challenges of scaling technical, engineering, and manufacturing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of strategic pedigree—you have either scaled successfully with a high-growth startup OR you have navigated company downfalls and possess a deep, analytical understanding of &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; things go wrong and how to prevent it.&lt;/li&gt;
