&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated Manufacturing Test Engineer to join our Powertrain Manufacturing team. This role focuses on the development, implementation, and continuous improvement of in-line and end-of-line testing for electric drive units (EDUs), stators, and rotors in a production environment. The engineer will work closely with cross-functional teams including design, quality, and production to ensure testing systems are robust, reliable, and aligned with manufacturing and product performance requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and manage test specifications, parameters, and acceptance criteria to ensure functional and quality compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze test data, diagnose failures, and implement root cause analysis and corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement of testing processes through data-driven analysis, process optimization, and feedback loops with manufacturing engineering and quality teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train maintenance and production teams on test equipment operation and troubleshooting procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the end-to-end sourcing and implementation of a high-volume electric drive unit EOL test rig, including scope definition, RFQ generation, vendor evaluation and selection, and technical/commercial alignment with internal stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee vendor management through design, build, FAT/SAT, and on-site commissioning, ensuring successful integration and production launch at the manufacturing facility with full adherence to safety, quality, and throughput requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Mechatronics, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-10+ years of experience in test engineering, preferably in electric powertrain or automotive manufacturing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience with specifying, sourcing, and launching automated test equipment in a high-volume environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with test automation, data acquisition systems, and industrial instrumentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of statistical process control (SPC) and design of experiments (DOE) methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills; ability to work in a fast-paced, collaborative environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Benefits &amp;amp; Perks:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
